		<h3>Product Review</h3>
		<p>
			Once upon a time, consumers had only two options to
			choose between when it came to peanut butter: chunky or creamy.  
			Today, there are so many different types of
			peanut butters on the market, ranging from 100% organic ground
			peanuts to reduced-fat, no-stir, flavoured peanut butter
			with marshmallow bits inside.  
			The peanut butter I used in my recipe was the first
			one I have seen that's protein-fortified with
			whey protein isolate.  
			And let me tell you, it was yummy!  
			Introducing the 	
					<a
						href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B00B99OJ26/?tag=lich048-20"
						class="amazon">
						white chocolate-flavoured high protein Peanut Butter spread</a>, from
					<a
						href="https://www.p28foods.com/">P28 Foods
					</a>. 
					With 14g of protein per 2 tbsp-serving, this is a highly nutritious spread! 
		</p>
